<FONT FACE="Calibri, Verdana, Helvetica, Arial"><SPAN STYLE='font-size:11pt'>Not exactly, it depends on what you push up the stack. If you push just an error code, than you are right, there is very little value. &nbsp;However, if you push up the error strings (or something like that), and have an upper layer interact with SLURM or Moab&#8217;s error reporting system, the btl&#8217;s don&#8217;t need to learn about and depend on a new interface.<BR>
<BR>
Rich<BR>
<BR>
