On 12/4/08 12:47 PM, &quot;Brian W. Barrett&quot; &lt;<a href="brbarret@open-mpi.org">brbarret@open-mpi.org</a>&gt; wrote:<BR>
<BR>
</SPAN></FONT><BLOCKQUOTE><FONT FACE="Calibri, Verdana, Helvetica, Arial"><SPAN STYLE='font-size:11pt'>That was my thought exactly. &nbsp;And since the point of the notifier<BR>
component is to return a *useful* description of what failure the BTL had<BR>
(like IB ran out of resource X again), that will be lost if we just push<BR>
that up to the next layer.<BR>
<BR>
Just my $0.02, of course.<BR>
